{
  "stem": "9963.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We started early morning, when it come time in the morning to say our prayers, we stop studying, and we say our prayers.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we didn't ate nothing, and just went back to the Talmud, you know, to the studying.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because you see, you understand, to study in the Talmud it's very much involved.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It involves what you have to look at a part of that and part of the [NON-ENGLISH] and something else, in order to prepare the different ideas and come out, you know, to the [NON-ENGLISH], and to know what you're learning about, what you understand.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It is not simple.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It is very mind-boggling to learn the Talmud.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was very deep, deep thoughts-- deep things to answer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It is very, very hard.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, when you learn, and you understand, it is very rewarding.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It is very rewarding.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I can tell you one thing that I now appreciated much more to my father, my parents, what they let me go to the yeshiva and to learn.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because it was so rewarding for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "A matter of fact, I can tell you what-- what that helped me a lot in my darkest days in my life, that helped me to survive, helped me, you know, to be a human being.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "To be there to myself, to do the things that other people didn't think that can be done.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I did it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I'm very appreciative even now what I learned.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I-- I can-- you know, go to the-- any synagogue and-- and be the, you know, a hassan, be a cantor, and they can tell you things and to-- say their prayers.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I-- and I understand every word what I'm saying.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That's the most important thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
